{{DISPLAYTITLE:Digital Skills Global}} {{COI|date=November 2018}} {{Advert|date=November 2018}} {{Use Irish English|date=March 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox University | |name =Digital Skills Global |native_name = |image_name = |former_names =Digital Skills Academy |established =2008 |type = |free_label = CEO |free = Paul Dunne |students = |city =[[Dublin]] |country =[[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] |website =https://digitalskillsglobal.com |affiliations =[[Dublin Institute of Technology]] [[Boston College]] |logo = }}
'''Digital Skills Global''', formerly '''Digital Skills Academy''' is a provider of [[Third-level education in the Republic of Ireland|higher education programs]] and courses for working professionals. The Academy offers a range of programs including online international BSc Degrees, Professional Certificates and Short Courses. Graduates are located in 33 countries across six continents and work for organisations such as [[Google]], [[PayPal]], [[Facebook]], [[LinkedIn]], [[Deloitte]], [[IBM]] and [[Ernst & Young|EY]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://it-online.co.za/2017/04/05/digital-skills-academy-steps-up-global-growth/|title=Digital Skills Academy steps up global growth|date=2017-04-05|work=IT-Online|access-date=2017-10-23|language=en-US}}</ref>
== History == Educator and entrepreneur Paul Dunne founded Digital Skills Academy in 2008.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://businessandfinance.com/the-digital-agenda/|title=The digital agenda|date=2013-07-10|work=Business & Finance|access-date=2017-10-23|language=en-GB}}</ref> In 2011, [[Dublin Institute of Technology|Dublin Institute of Technology (DIT)]] and Digital Skills Academy signed an agreement to develop and deliver new digital skills training programs, commencing with WebElevate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.siliconrepublic.com/careers/dit-and-digital-skills-academy-form-partnership|title=DIT and Digital Skills Academy form partnership - Careers {{!}} siliconrepublic.com - Ireland's Technology News Service|last=silicon|date=2011-08-02|work=Silicon Republic|access-date=2017-10-23|language=en-GB}}</ref> Subsequent programs included WebInnovate,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://irishtechnews.ie/digital-skills-academy-sows-the-seeds-of-success-for-digital-entrepreneurs/|title=Digital Skills Academy Sows the Seeds of Success for Digital Entrepreneurs! – Irish Tech News|website=irishtechnews.ie|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-23}}</ref> WebActivate<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.siliconrepublic.com/careers/webactivate-digital-skills-training-programme-launches-to-upskill-job-seekers|title=WebActivate digital skills training programme launches to upskill job seekers - Careers {{!}} siliconrepublic.com - Ireland's Technology News Service|last=Doyle|first=Carmel|date=2013-02-06|work=Silicon Republic|access-date=2017-10-23|language=en-GB}}</ref> and TechElevate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.prodigylearning.com/news-events/75-launch-of-techelevate-with-mta|title=Prodigy Learning {{!}} News & Events {{!}} Launch of TechElevate with MTA|website=www.prodigylearning.com|access-date=2017-10-23}}</ref>
In October 2015, Digital Skills Academy launched its online BSc Honours Degree in Digital Technology Design and Innovation<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/digital-skills-academy-launches-worlds-first-online-degree-in-integrated-digital-technology-business-and-design-509308931.html|title=Digital Skills Academy Launches World's First Online Degree in Integrated Digital Technology, Business and Design|last=Academy|first=Digital Skills|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-23}}</ref> and the online BSc Degree in Digital Technology and Design followed in March 2016. Data Science<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.siliconrepublic.com/advice/data-sciences-courses-online-learning-skills|title=6 online data science courses to launch your career|last=Darmody|first=Jenny|date=2017-07-11|work=Silicon Republic|access-date=2017-10-23|language=en-GB}}</ref> and Digital Marketing stream specializations were added to the online BSc Honours Degree in Digital Technology Design and Innovation program in April 2017.
The Academy launched its Professional Diploma in Digital Innovation in May 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.co.uk/news-releases/dont-look-abroad-for-skilled-employees-upskill-existing-staff---digital-skills-academy-618065343.html|title=Don't Look Abroad for Skilled Employees; Upskill Existing Staff - Digital Skills Academy|last=Academy|first=Digital Skills|website=www.prnewswire.co.uk|access-date=2017-10-23}}</ref> In October 2017, The Academy launched an extensive portfolio of Online Short Courses (initially 25) in digital technology, digital business, design, and innovation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.co.uk/news-releases/digital-skills-academy-answers-industrys-call-for-improved-digital-training-651390103.html|title=Digital Skills Academy Answers Industry's Call for Improved Digital Training|last=Academy|first=Digital Skills|website=www.prnewswire.co.uk|access-date=2017-10-23}}</ref>
In October 2018, Boston College Global Leadership Institute, in collaboration with Digital Skills Global, launched a range of industry-aligned Professional Certificates in Digital Skills in fields including digital business, digital marketing, data science and coding.{{cn|date=November 2018}}
Digital Skills Academy re-branded to Digital Skills Global in November 2018. {{cn|date=November 2018}}
== Location == Digital Skills Global headquarters is located in the [[The Digital Hub|Digital Hub]], Dublin, Ireland. The Academy also has offices in New York, United States, Johannesburg, South Africa<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ee.co.za/article/online-degree-integrated-digital-technology-business-design.html|title=Online degree in integrated digital technology, business and design - EE Publishers|date=2015-09-28|work=EE Publishers|access-date=2017-10-23|language=en-GB}}</ref> and London, United Kingdom.
== Certification == The certificates for the Digital Skills Global Professional Certificates in Digital Skills are awarded by [[Boston College|Boston College Global Leadership Institute]].{{cn|date=November 2018}}
== Accreditation == The degree programs that Digital Skills Global are currently delivering are accredited by Dublin Institute of Technology (DIT). DIT participates as a full member of the [[European University Association]] (EUA) and the [[International Association of Universities]] (IAU).
